ABC Corp. is formalized and centralized. ABC Corp.'s processes are well-documented, and each employee's job description is set. Company formalization is high. Centralization is the extent to which an organization's leadership makes decisions. The ABC Corp. CEO is in charge, and a few managers report to him. High centralization means low-level workers have less decision-making power. The company's strong formalization and centralization may be due to its modest size, stable environment, and product supplied to other enterprises. This establishes a clear chain of command and streamlines decision-making, helping the organization retain consistency and efficiency. 